15. SERVICE DESCRIPTION
========================================================

Ion Drift is an open-source network monitoring and management
platform for MikroTik RouterOS environments. The source code is
publicly available under the PolyForm Shield 1.0.0 license. The
Software provides real-time device discovery, behavioral
analysis, topology mapping, connection tracking, policy
deviation detection, alerting, and reporting capabilities as
described at https://www.mycyberhive.com.

The Software is primarily observational. It reads data from
your network equipment via API and SNMP. The Software does
not modify NAT rules, routing tables, bridge configurations,
DHCP settings, DNS settings, or any traffic-altering
configuration.

The Software includes an optional provisioning feature that,
with your explicit approval, creates the following on your
MikroTik router:

  a. MANGLE RULES. Passthrough mangle rules to count
     inter-VLAN and WAN traffic flows. These are passthrough
     counters only — they do not filter, redirect, drop, or
     alter packet flow in any way.

  b. SYSLOG ACTION. A remote logging action that directs
     firewall log messages to the Software's syslog listener
     for connection tracking analysis.

  c. LOGGING RULE. A logging rule that routes the "firewall"
     log topic to the syslog action created above.

  d. FIREWALL LOG RULES. Firewall filter rules in the
     "forward" and "input" chains with action "log" that
     log new connections with an identifying prefix. These
     rules log only — they do not filter, drop, reject, or
     alter any traffic. They are appended to the end of
     their respective chains.

Provisioning is never automatic. It requires the user to:
(1) explicitly trigger a scan; (2) review the proposed
changes in detail, including the exact JSON payloads that
will be sent to the router; and (3) approve each change
before it is applied. All provisioned rules and actions are
identified with an "iondrift" or "ion-drift" label and can
be removed at any time through your router's management
interface. The Software does not modify or delete existing
router rules or configuration.

Feature availability depends on network hardware, configuration,
and the specific license tier purchased. Cyber Hive Security LLC
does not guarantee compatibility with all network environments
or hardware configurations.

